glosses: To increase, to grow in amount or number, to multiply.

etymology:
Inherited from Ottoman Turkish چوغالمق (çoğalmaḳ), from چوق (çoḳ), equivalent to
çok (“many, much”) + -al (verb-forming suffix) + -mak. Cognate with Azerbaijani çoxalmaq, Kyrgyz чогулуу (coguluu), Karakhanid چُقْرَشْماقْ (çoḳraşmaḳ).
